Listens via Slack Socket Mode for messages and dispatches Claude to solve tickets.
In channels, @mention the bot. In DMs, just send a message.

Usage:
  ticket-bot              Start the bot (runs in foreground)
  ticket-bot --mock       Skip AI, use dummy changes (for testing the pipeline)
  ticket-bot --help       Show this help

Slack commands (DM or @mention in a channel):
  UB-1234                           Start working on a ticket
  UB-1234 <slack-url>               Include Slack thread as context
  UB-1234 extra instructions here   Add context for Claude
  <slack-url>                       Solve from Slack thread (no Jira ticket)
  <slack-url> extra instructions    Slack thread + extra context
  help                              Show usage in Slack
  status                            List active/completed jobs

Thread replies:
  - Claude may ask questions mid-work — reply to unblock it
  - After completion, reply with feedback to trigger another pass

State is saved to ~/.cache/ticket-solve/*.json
Logs are at ~/.cache/ticket-solve/*.log

Dependencies:
  pip install -r requirements.txt   (or: pip install slack_sdk)

Requires in .env:
  TICKET_CREATOR_BOT_TOKEN   Slack bot token (xoxb-...)
  SLACK_APP_TOKEN             Slack app-level token (xapp-...)
