Slack app setup:
  1. Create a Slack app at https://api.slack.com/apps
  2. Enable Socket Mode (Settings → Socket Mode → Enable)
  3. Generate an App-Level Token with connections:write scope
     → this is your SLACK_APP_TOKEN (starts with xapp-)
  4. Add bot token scopes (OAuth & Permissions → Scopes → Bot Token Scopes):
       chat:write, files:write, channels:history, channels:read,
       groups:history, groups:read, im:history, reactions:read
  5. Subscribe to bot events (Event Subscriptions → Subscribe to bot events):
       message.channels, message.groups, message.im, reaction_added
  6. Enable Interactivity (Features → Interactivity & Shortcuts → toggle on)
     → required for the "Create Jira ticket" button + modal on slack-thread jobs.
       With Socket Mode you can leave the Request URL blank.
  7. Install the app to your workspace
     → copy the Bot User OAuth Token as TICKET_CREATOR_BOT_TOKEN (starts with xoxb-)
  8. Invite the bot to any channels you want it to listen in: /invite @botname
""")
    sys.exit(0)

