# The "Create Jira ticket" button + modal on slack-thread jobs only work
# when Slack's *Interactivity* feature is turned on for this app. That's
# a UI toggle with no scope backing it, so auth.test can't report it, and
# the only API that can (apps.manifest.export) needs a short-lived
# App Configuration Token that's not worth the rotation overhead for a
# startup check. Just nag the operator once so they know the gotcha
# exists; if they've already flipped it on, the message is harmless.

